dct_title_s: Northern Israel structural map on top Judea Group (Sheet 2)
dct_description_sm: Geophysical Institute of Israel. Companion text: Appendix C: Top Judea Group - Digital structural map of Israel / Lorian Fleischer and Rina Gafsou. Geological framework of the Levant. Volume I: Cyprus and Syria. Volume II: The Levantine Basin and Israel / John K. Hall; Valey A. Krasheninnikov; Francis Hirsch; Chaim Benjamini; Akiva Flexer. Jerusalem: Historical Productions-Hall. Vol II. 2005. 745-754 p. North Decimal Degree 31.433300. South Decimal Degree 31.300. East Decimal Degree 35.8833. West Decimal Degree 34.3000. Prepared for the Ministry of National Infrastructures. Job no. 753/312/2003. Recto: Map shows structure with 100 m. contour and hypsometric tints. Ancillary map: [Israel shaded relief]. Verso: structure is shown with 50 m. contour. 2003
